headline: Will Dover's (DOV) Updated 2025 Guidance and Expansion Plans Shift Its Growth Narrative?
summary: Dover Corporation recently reported its third quarter 2025 financial results and confirmed full-year guidance, projecting GAAP EPS from continuing operations between US$8.06 and US$8.16, with revenue growth of 4% to 6% for the year. While sales increased year-over-year in the third quarter, net income declined, alongside news that Dover Food Retail will invest over US$20 million to expand its Virginia operations and create more than 300 new jobs.
